This paper discusses the use of pre-print repositories and the development of applications to assist the scientific community, which falls under the scope of digital libraries (cs.DL). The paper also discusses the use of metadata and social-network algorithms for peer-review, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and social networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of metadata tags, which could fall under the category of cyberinfrastructure (cs.CY) or software development (cs.SD).
